  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This was a single-site RCT to assess the effect of a longitudinal mindfulness intervention on&#xD;
      burnout for first-year (PGY-1) internal medicine (IM) and pediatrics residents. The primary&#xD;
      outcome was Maslach Burnout Inventory MBI) scores at baseline and 12 month follow-up.&#xD;
      Secondary outcomes were feasibility and perceived benefit of the intervention.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
